<m0>AROUND DADE<ql>
<ue5>We Will Rebuild donates to homeless<ql>
<ue5><ep>
   <m0>We Will Rebuild <m0>has approved a $250,000 grant for the Community Partnership for the Homeless to help build a 300-bed Homeless Assistance Center on the Homestead Air Reserve Base.<ep>
   Part of the money, $75,000, is earmarked specifically for housing for migrant farmworkers.<ep>
   The Community Partnership is a private, nonprofit agency designated by the Dade County Homeless Trust to operate up to three assistance centers for the homeless. The first is at 1550 N. Miami Ave. Zoning hearings on the second center are scheduled for June.<ql>
<ql>
<m1><styl>rdup,,24<ql>
<m0>GOVERNMENT IN ACTION<ql>
<ue5>Drug Court to receive $300,000<ql>
<ue5><m1><styl>indentl,2l,0,3p3,3p3<ql>
<m0><ep>
   WASHINGTON (--) The Justice Department will grant Metro-Dade County $300,000 to improve its <m0>drug court <m0>for nonviolent offenders, Attorney General Janet Reno announced Thursday.<ep>
  Reno, who advocated the drug program as Dade state attorney, announced the award as part of an $8.5 million grant to 16 communities around the country.<ep>
  Drug court requires offenders to undergo periodic testing and substance abuse treatment. Offenders who fail are subject to additional sanctions, including jail.<ep>
   ``These courts are making a difference,'' Reno said at her regular Justice Department news briefing, where officials cited a study of the nation's first drug court in Miami as revealing a 30 percent reduction in rearrests for drug court graduates compared with nondrug court offenders.<ql>
<ql>
<m1><styl>rdup,,24<ql>
<m0><ue5>Fund started for crash victims' families<ql>
<ue5><ep>
   Employers of the four men killed in a massive auto wreck Thursday have started a fund for the victims' families.<ep>
   Four lawn maintenance workers, Bonafaccio Navarro, 66, Carlos Mejia (also known as Santos Vertis), 22, Jean Claude Rodolphe, 45, and Jose Gaspar, 30, were killed Thursday morning as they drove along <m0>Card Sound Road <m0>headed for work. A truck traveling in the opposite direction lost control, turning over on top of Mejia's car.<ep>
   The men were all employees of Tropics North, a commercial landscaping company.<ep>
    Contributions may be sent to The Trust Account for the Surviving Families, Tropics North Inc., c/o Community Bank, 28801 SW 157th Ave., Homestead, Fla. 33033. The account number is: 010124032020.<ep>
