<styl>rdup,,24<ql>
<ue5><m0>Street named for man killed in Croatia<ql>
<m1><ue5><styl>MUGr<ql>
Conrad<ue5><ql>
<ep>
<m0>   <m0>Barry L. Conrad, <m0>the Dade businessman who died in the crash of a U.S. government plane in Croatia last month, will have a street named in his memory in a ceremony Monday.<ep>
   The five blocks, on Southwest 94th Street from 87th to 92nd avenues, will be named Barry L. Conrad Drive. The street runs past Baptist Hospital, to which Conrad was a contributor, said an aide to Metro Commissioner Miguel Diaz de la Portilla, who sponsored the resolution.<ep>
   ``He was very enthusiastic about our community and lent his time and leadership skills in support of many of our local organizations and charities,'' Diaz de la Portilla said in a statement.<ep>
   Conrad, founder of The Barrington Group and a former president at Miami-based Burger King, was a passenger on the ill-fated plane carrying U.S. Commerce Secretary Ron Brown on a trade mission April 3.<ep>
   <m4>Conrad<m2><ql>
<m0>The renaming ceremony will take place at 2 p.m. at Southwest 87th Avenue and 94th Street.<ql>
