<m0>ON THE STREETS<ql>
<ue5>Mother of boys left alone still missing<ql>
<ue5><m1><styl>indentl,2l,0,3p3,3p3<ql>
<m0><ep>
   <m0>Miami Beach <m0>police continue to search for the mother who left two boys alone in an apartment for five hours Thursday.<ep>
   Officials from Dade's Department of Health and Rehabilitative Services appeared in court Friday to officially place the boys (--) age 3 months and 3 years (--) in court custody, said HRS spokesman Imran Ali.<ep>
   ``The boys appear to be well physically,'' Ali said. ``But the basic fact that they were left alone makes this a case of neglect.''<ep>
   A neighbor notified HRS on Thursday when she discovered the boys alone inside an apartment in the 8100 block of Crespi Boulevard in North Beach. The mother was last seen about 8 a.m. Thursday. <ep>
   Officials are having difficulty locating family members, and no father is listed on the birth certificates of the children, whose last name is Espinoza.<ep>
   HRS had previously investigated the family, Ali said, but he would not comment on the reasons.<ql>
